query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `export_history` (
  `id` varchar(64) PRIMARY KEY,
  `userId` varchar(64) NOT NULL,
  `projectId` int,
  `pesquisaId` int,
  `context` text,
  `filters` json,
  `format` enum('csv','excel','pdf') NOT NULL,
  `outputType` enum('list','report') NOT NULL,
  `recordCount` int DEFAULT 0 NOT NULL,
  `fileUrl` text,
  `fileSize` int DEFAULT 0,
  `generationTime` int DEFAULT 0,
  `createdAt` timestamp DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  INDEX `idx_export_user` (`userId`),
  INDEX `idx_export_project` (`projectId`),
  INDEX `idx_export_created` (`createdAt`),
  FOREIGN KEY (`userId`) REFERENCES `users`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  FOREIGN KEY (`projectId`) REFERENCES `projects`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  FOREIGN KEY (`pesquisaId`) REFERENCES `pesquisas`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE
)
